<MainLayout title="About">
  <article class="grid_1-1">
    <div>
      <h2 id="h2_1">2024</h2>
      <p>
        Karrusel, Copenhagen, Refshaleøen fra d. 22–24 August 2024 3 days of
        house, disco, and techno in the magical forest. Karrusel takes place at
        a secluded green spot on Refshaleøen in central Copenhagen. Address:
        Refshalevej 193, 1432 Copenhagen. Early Bird Festival Passes on sale now
        until 1 April.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>THANKS</h2>
      <p>
        Special thanks to each and every volunteer, Heineken Silver for
        supporting new and wild ideas and Refshaleøen for meeting our housing
        needs.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>FESTIVAL EXPERIENCE</h2>
      <p>
        Karrusel believes in the right to a harassment-free festival experience.
        We believe in the right of everyone to express themselves. Karrusel
        welcomes everybody – all with their different orientations, experiences,
        histories and backgrounds. Karrusel only exists if everyone takes care
        of each other, respects their own and others boundaries, embraces
        diversity and acts as a part of the community.
      </p><br />
      <p>
        If you feel unsafe, please reach out to our awareness team. They will be
        wearing a pink vests and walk around the site and be at their base (see
        on this map). Ask any festival staff and they will guide you to the
        them.
      </p>
      <p>Take responsibility for your own actions.</p>
      <p>Respect your own and others boundaries.</p>
      <p>Speak up rather than look the other way.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <img src="../../imgs/about/img1.webp" alt="Karrusel by night" />
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>SUSTAINABILITY</h2>
      <p>
        Karrusel is committed to becoming more sustainable. In order to save
        resources and reduce waste we use left over materials and timber for
        stage designs and installations. We will re-use production and print
        materials when possible year after year. Beverages are served in
        reusable or sustainable materials. Straws are not being used.
      </p><br />
      <p>
        How you can help: Take a bike or public transport to the festival. Don’t
        bring confetti or glitter to the festival. There will be free tap water
        stations during the festival. Please bring an empty cup or bottle and
        drink nice free tap water.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <img src="../../imgs/about/img2.webp" alt="Artists by night" />
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>HISTORY</h2>
      <p>
        2024 marks the 5th edition of Karrusel. Karrusel is a circus themed rave
        presenting some of the world's leading electronic artists. Past editions
        include performances by Acid Pauli, Amelie Lens, Dixon, FJAAK, Folamour,
        Hunee, Job Jobse, Kölsch, Mall Grab, Nastia, Partiboi69, Peggy Gou,
        Richie Hawtin, Skin On Skin, The Blessed Madonna, Victor Ruiz and VTSS.
        The festival is open air and takes place on secluded green spot at the
        abandoned shipyard of Refshaleøen in central Copenhagen.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <img src="../../imgs/about/img3.webp" alt="Party crowd" />
    </div>
  </article>
</MainLayout>
